The latest data from Johns Hopkins University shows the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases worldwide has surpassed 262 million, with over 5.2 million deaths. Here is the latest: The Chinese mainland recorded 113 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Tuesday, with 91 linked to local transmissions and 22 from overseas. The WHO warned on Tuesday that blanket travel bans will not prevent the international spread of the COVID-19 variant Omicron, even as dozens of countries have already introduced such restrictions. South Korea reported a new daily record of 5,123 new coronavirus cases as the country battles to contain a sharp rise in patients with severe symptoms and stave off the Omicron variant, the Korea Disease Control and Prevention Agency (KDCA) said on Wednesday. Japan will ban the entry of non-resident foreigners over concerns of the rapidly-spreading Omicron variant, effective November 30.